<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Two fragments which almost certainly join: a, the upper left corner (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.24</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.39</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.31</measure>) and b, the upper right corner and the lower part, of a <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> with simple moulding above. '<foreign lang="fr">Largeur de la base 0.44</foreign>'.

</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the two fasciae of the moulding (ll.1 and 2) and on the base (3 ff.). </p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>: 'H. de lettres <measure dim="none">0.04</measure>' (a), but it is clear that the letters in l.2 are smaller than the others. <foreign lang="grc">ΝΗ</foreign> in ligature, l. 4; stop for abbreviations.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0151" notAfter="0200">Second half of second century A.D.</date>
(<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">monument group</rs>, <rs type="criteria">prosopography</rs>).</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Σεκουνδίλλα">Σεκούνδιλλα</name><lb n="2"/><w>θυγατὴρ</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Σέκουνδος">Σεκούν<lb n="3"/>δου</name>  <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w>  <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Ἀπολλώνιος">Ἀπολ<lb n="4" type="worddiv"/>λωνίου</name></persName></persName></persName>  <w>γύ<hi rend="ligature">νη</hi></w>  <lb n="5"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Τιβέριος" type="praenomen"><expan><abbr>Τι<orig><g type="stop"/></orig></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">βερίου</supplied></expan></name>  <name reg="Κλαύδιος"><expan><abbr>Κλ<orig><g type="stop"/></orig></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αυδίου</supplied></expan></name>  <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Κλαύδιος"><expan><abbr>Κλ<orig><g type="stop"/></orig></abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αυδίου</supplied></expan></name>    <name reg="Ἀντίοχος">Ἀντι<lb n="6" type="worddiv"/>όχου</name></persName>  <w>ἀρχιερέ<lb n="7" type="worddiv"/>ως </w><w>υἵου</w> <name reg="Ἀντίοχος">Ἀντι<lb n="8" type="worddiv"/>όχου</name></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">τῇ</w> <w lemma="πατρίς">Πά<lb n="9" type="worddiv"/><space extent="2" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>τριδι</w>    <g type="leaf"/>  <lb n="10"/></ab>
</div>


<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Secundilla, daughter of Secundus the son of Apollonios, wife of Ti<supplied reason="abbreviation">berius</supplied> Cl<supplied reason="abbreviation">audius</supplied> Antiochos, the son of Cl<supplied reason="abbreviation">audius</supplied> Antiochos, high priest, to her homeland.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>One of the series of dedications from the East Court of the Hadrianic Baths: <xref type="iAph">1183</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1184</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1186</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1187</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1188</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1189</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1190</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1191</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1192</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1193</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1194</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1195</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1197</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1198</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1199</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1200</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1201</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1202</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1203</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1204</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1205</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1206</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1207</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1208</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1209</xref>, <xref type="iAph">1210</xref> ; all are by women, and apparently bore caryatids (see <xref type="iAph">1198</xref>).</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p>
Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Hadrianic Baths, East Court</rs>: 'Cour de l'E(st). Partie Nord' (Boulanger)</rs>
<rs type="origLocation"><rs type="monuList">Hadrianic Baths</rs>: ?Caryatid portico</rs>
; Last known location: <rs type="lastLocation">a Museum; b Findspot (1905)</rs>
</p>
</div>
